In fragile splendor, 
each dawn approach,
preambles breathe the music of seasons— 
woven in the fabric of day, the worlds intertwine,
softly, as light touches
the iridescence of the breeze.
True beauty lives in these moments, 
as nature sings the unsung lullabies.

- Paul Valéry  


- Paul Valéry
